<header class="header">
  <h1>Is It Too Late to Plant Cucumbers?</h1>

  <p class="tagline">
    Cucumbers grow quickly — but frost ends them immediately.
  </p>

  <p class="lede">
    <strong>Whether it’s too late to plant cucumbers depends on how many frost-free days and growing degree days (GDD) remain in your season.</strong>
  </p>

  <p>
    Cucumbers are one of the fastest-growing summer vegetables.
    Many gardeners plant them in succession after early crops finish.
  </p>

  <p>
    In warm mid-summer soil, cucumbers often grow faster than they do in spring.
  </p>

  <p>
    However, they are extremely frost sensitive.
    Even a light frost can kill vines and end production immediately.
  </p>

  <p>
    The real question isn’t the month —
    it’s whether your location still has enough heat before first fall frost
    for cucumbers to mature.
  </p>

  <p>
    Use the calculator below to check your planting date and location.
  </p>
</header>

